1. About this Policy
This Policy describes how we process your and your child's personal data when using Spotify Kids. The aim of this Policy is to explain how Spotify gives your child a great experience when using Spotify Kids, and in particular to:
Ensure that you understand what personal data we collect about you and your child when using Spotify Kids, the reasons why we collect and use it, and who we share it with;
Explain the additional privacy and security measures and controls we have implemented for Spotify Kids in order to provide a good environment for your child; and
Explain the available rights and choices in relation to the personal data we collect and process about you and your child when using Spotify Kids, and how we will protect the privacy of your child.
This information can also be found in our
Kids resource
, designed to be understood by the older children using Spotify Kids.
The
Spotify® Premium for Family Terms and Conditions
is a separate document outlining the legal contract between you and Spotify for using the Spotify Premium Family Plan, including Spotify Kids.
2. Parental controls and security
We are committed to protecting your and your child's personal data. We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to help protect the security of your child's personal data; however, be aware that no system is ever completely secure. We have implemented various policies including pseudonymization, encryption, access, and retention policies to guard against unauthorised access and unnecessary retention of personal data in our systems.
To help ensure a good environment for your child when using Spotify Kids, we've also implemented the following controls:
Parental protection
- in order to access and enable certain functions in Spotify Kids, such as creating or deleting a child's account and changing the account settings, you as a parent need to provide a verification code. This allows you to control what features your child may use on Spotify Kids and prevents your child from changing settings by themselves.
Appropriate content
- Spotify Kids will only contain age-appropriate content, selected by our editors. At account setup, you will have the option to select what kind of content your child's Spotify Kids account should contain.
In the
Spotify Privacy Policy
you can learn more about the rights and preferences applicable to any of your personal data which is processed by Spotify. You can, at any time, access the personal data associated with the Spotify Kids account. In addition, you can always request that we delete the personal data associated with the Spotify Kids account. If you request deletion of your own Spotify account, the personal data associated with the Spotify Kids account will automatically be deleted.
If you have any questions about your child's privacy, your rights, or how to exercise them, please contact our Data Protection Officer using the "
Contact Us
" form on the Privacy Center. We will respond to your request within a reasonable period of time upon verification of your identity. You also have the right to contact the
Swedish Authority for Privacy Protection
or your local data protection authority about any questions or concerns.
3. Personal data we collect about you and your child
These tables set out the categories of personal data we collect and use.
Collected when you sign up for the Spotify Kids Service
or when you update your account
Categories of personal data
Description of category
User Data
Personal data that we need to create your Spotify Kids account and which enables you and your child to use Spotify Kids. This includes your child’s name. You also have the option to provide us with your child’s birthdate and select a color and an avatar in order to make your child’s Spotify Kids account more personalized. In addition, we use the country you provided in your Spotify account.
Collected through your use of the Spotify Kids Service
Categories of personal data
Description of category
Usage Data
Personal data collected about you and your child when you’re accessing and/or using Spotify Kids:
Information about how you use Spotify Kids including your actions with Spotify Kids, such as date and time of content you have listened to or saved, search queries, and account settings.
Your technical data, for example:
URL information,
IP addresses,
information about devices you use such as: device IDs, network connection type (e.g. WiFi, 3G, LTE, Bluetooth) and provider, network and device performance, browser type, language, information enabling digital rights management, operating system, and Spotify application version.
Your general (non-precise) location. This is understood from technical data (e.g. your IP address or language setting of your device) and is needed to meet geographic requirements in our agreements with owners of content on Spotify Kids.
Collected from third party sources
Categories of personal data
Description of category
Third party applications and devices you connect to your Spotify Kids account
If you connect your Spotify Kids account to a third party application and/or device(s), we may collect certain information from them to make the integration possible.
We will only collect personal data from these third parties when you as a parent allow us to do so, e.g. by selecting the appropriate setting, allowing bluetooth connection on the device, and/or by providing your consent.
Technical service partners
We work with technical service partners that give us certain data, such as mapping IP addresses to non-precise location data (e.g., city, state, or post code).
This makes it possible for us to provide Spotify Kids content and features.
